{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AEfqTGEsXwzkyTAE2K8sYh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current state. The route `GET /projects/{name}/runs` already exists (line 143 of handler.go) with `handleProjectRuns`. The old route `GET /runs` with `?project=` query param also exists (line 140).\n\nLooking at the templates, the runs.html template's `filterByProject` JS function already redirects to `/projects/<label>/runs` when a label is found (line 65), but falls back to `/runs?project=` (line 67).\n\nThe task says to move the URL from `runs?project=...` to `projects/<project>/runs`. The route already exists. I need to:\n\n\n1. Remove the fallback to `/runs?project=` in the runs.html template JS\n2. Check if there are any other references to the old URL pattern\n\nLet me search through the handler tests and other files to see where else the old query parameter pattern might be used.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26195,"cache_read_input_tokens":15177,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":26195},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a2f2d67-cd96-47e8-94d1-4bd9c3759ba4","uuid":"075352a1-55bb-42be-8b7f-9602c263f968"}
